workflow.name: Automated customer support with GPT-4o-mini AI triage for Google Forms & Gmail
workflow.description:
Transform your Google Form into an intelligent customer support system that automatically analyzes, prioritizes, and responds to every inquiry with AI-powered personalization.

## Who's it for

This workflow is perfect for:

- **Customer support teams** handling high volumes of form submissions
- **Small businesses** looking to provide instant, professional responses 24/7
- **E-commerce stores** managing product inquiries, complaints, and refunds
- **Service providers** triaging appointment requests and support tickets
- **Event organizers** responding to registration questions

## How it works

When someone submits your Google Form, this workflow:

- **Triggers instantly** from new Google Sheets row
- **Analyzes with AI** to determine urgency (low/medium/high), category (technical/sales/support/billing), and sentiment (positive/neutral/negative)
- **Routes intelligently** based on priority level to appropriate response template
- **Generates personalized reply** using OpenAI, tailored to urgency and sentiment
- **Sends auto-reply** via Gmail with professional formatting
- **Alerts your team** on Slack for high-priority cases requiring human follow-up
- **Logs everything** to tracking sheet for analytics and audit trail

## Set up steps

**Time to set up:** approximately 15-20 minutes

### Prerequisites

- Google Form connected to Google Sheets
- OpenAI API key (get one at platform.openai.com)
- Gmail account for sending emails
- Slack workspace (optional, for team alerts)

### Configuration steps

1. **Connect Google Sheets Trigger** to your form response sheet
2. **Update column names** in "Map Form Column Names" node (default: Name, Email Address, Inquiry)
3. **Add OpenAI credentials** - uses GPT-4o-mini for cost efficiency (approximately $0.001 per inquiry)
4. **Connect Gmail** via OAuth2 for sending auto-replies
5. **Create tracking sheet** with columns: timestamp, name, email, urgency, category, sentiment, summary, keywords, subject, inquiry
6. **(Optional) Connect Slack** for high-priority notifications
7. **Test with sample data** before activating

## Requirements

- Google Form (free)
- Google Sheets (free)
- OpenAI API account (approximately $0.001-0.002 per inquiry with GPT-4o-mini)
- Gmail account (free)
- Slack workspace (optional, free tier available)
- n8n Cloud or self-hosted instance

## How to customize

**Adjust triage criteria:**

Edit the "Analyze with AI Triage" prompt to define what qualifies as high/medium/low urgency for your business. Add custom categories beyond the default five (technical/sales/support/billing/general).

**Modify response templates:**

Customize the three response generation nodes to match your brand voice. Add company-specific information, policies, or FAQ links. Adjust tone from formal to casual based on your audience.

**Add advanced features:**

- Insert CRM integration to check customer history before responding
- Add condition nodes to route specific categories to different team members
- Include file attachments (brochures, manuals) based on inquiry type
- Implement follow-up sequences with Wait nodes
- Connect multiple notification channels (Discord, email, SMS)

**Multi-language support:**

The AI automatically detects and responds in the inquiry's language. Customize prompts with language-specific instructions if needed.

## Use cases

- **Product support:** Auto-respond to "how to use" questions with relevant documentation
- **Complaint management:** Immediately acknowledge issues and alert team for urgent follow-up
- **Lead qualification:** Instantly engage sales inquiries while routing to appropriate sales rep
- **Appointment requests:** Confirm booking inquiries and provide next steps
- **Feedback collection:** Thank customers and categorize feedback for analysis

workflow.name: Automate Customer Support Responses with AI Triage for Google Forms

values.content:
=You are an expert customer support triage system with deep understanding of multiple languages and cultural context.

Analyze this customer inquiry:

Customer Name: {{$json["Name"]}}
Customer Email: {{$json["Email Address"]}}
Inquiry: {{$json.inquiry}}

URGENCY CLASSIFICATION RULES (be strict):

HIGH urgency - Use when ANY of these apply:
- Product is broken/damaged/defective
- Words indicating immediate need: immediately, urgent, ASAP
- Customer explicitly states they are troubled or frustrated
- Complaints or angry tone
- Request for refund/replacement/exchange
- Service failure or system down
- Time-sensitive issues

MEDIUM urgency - Use when:
- General questions about product usage
- Feature inquiries or clarifications
- Manual/documentation questions
- Non-urgent support requests
- Neutral tone inquiries

LOW urgency - Use when:
- General information requests
- Compliments or positive feedback
- Future product inquiries
- Casual questions with no time pressure

CATEGORIES:
- technical: Software bugs, technical issues, errors, login problems
- sales: Pricing, product information, purchase inquiries
- support: How-to questions, usage help, troubleshooting
- billing: Payment issues, invoices, refunds
- general: Everything else

SENTIMENT:
- negative: Complaints, problems, dissatisfaction, frustrated tone
- neutral: Questions, information requests
- positive: Compliments, satisfaction, thank you messages

Return ONLY valid JSON in this format (no markdown, no code blocks):
{
  "urgency": "low" | "medium" | "high",
  "category": "technical" | "sales" | "support" | "billing" | "general",
  "sentiment": "positive" | "neutral" | "negative",
  "keywords": ["keyword1", "keyword2"],
  "summary": "One sentence summary"
}

parameters.content:
## üìã AI-Powered Customer Support Automation

**Automatically triage and respond to Google Form submissions with intelligent priority routing**

### üéØ What This Workflow Does

This workflow transforms your Google Form into an intelligent customer support system that:
- **Analyzes** every inquiry using AI to determine urgency, category, and sentiment
- **Routes** inquiries based on priority (High/Medium/Low)
- **Generates** contextual, personalized email responses
- **Alerts** your team via Slack for high-priority cases
- **Tracks** all interactions in a Google Sheet

### ‚öôÔ∏è How It Works

1. **Trigger**: Monitors Google Sheets for new form responses
2. **AI Analysis**: OpenAI analyzes inquiry for urgency, category, sentiment
3. **Smart Routing**: Routes to appropriate response template
4. **Response Generation**: AI creates personalized reply email
5. **Auto-Reply**: Sends email via Gmail
6. **Team Alert**: Notifies team on Slack for urgent cases
7. **Tracking**: Logs all data to tracking sheet

### üì¶ Requirements

- Google Form connected to Google Sheets
- OpenAI API key (GPT-4o-mini recommended)
- Gmail account for sending emails
- Slack workspace (optional, for team notifications)
- Google Sheets for tracking logs

### ‚è±Ô∏è Setup Time

Approximately **15-20 minutes**

### üöÄ Setup Steps

1. **Create Google Form** with fields: Name, Email Address, Inquiry
2. **Connect to Google Sheets** (automatically created by Google Forms)
3. **Configure trigger node** with your form response sheet
4. **Add OpenAI credentials** (get API key from platform.openai.com)
5. **Connect Gmail** for sending auto-replies
6. **Create tracking sheet** with columns: timestamp, name, email, category, urgency, sentiment, summary, keywords, subject, inquiry
7. **Optional: Connect Slack** for high-priority alerts
8. **Customize AI prompts** to match your brand voice and use case
9. **Test with sample data** before activating

### üé® Customization Options

- **Adjust urgency criteria** in AI Triage prompt for your specific needs
- **Modify response templates** for different priority levels
- **Add custom categories** (e.g., refunds, appointments, technical issues)
- **Multi-language support** - AI handles multiple languages automatically
- **Add more notification channels** (Discord, email, SMS)
- **Integrate with CRM** systems for customer history

### üí° Use Cases

- **Customer Support**: Auto-respond to product questions and issues
- **Lead Management**: Instant follow-up on sales inquiries
- **Event Registration**: Confirm bookings with personalized messages
- **Feedback Collection**: Acknowledge and categorize user feedback
- **Service Requests**: Triage and route service/maintenance requests

---

*Created by the n8n community. Questions? Check the sticky notes inside each workflow section for detailed instructions.*

### üì• Step 1: Form Response Trigger

Monitors your Google Sheet for new form submissions.

**Setup:**
1. Select your Google Form's response sheet
2. Sheet automatically updates when forms are submitted
3. Trigger runs every minute to check for new rows

**Requirements:**
- Google Form with fields: Name, Email Address, Inquiry
- Form must be connected to Google Sheets

### üîß Step 2: Map Column Names

Maps your form fields to workflow variables.

**Customize:**
- Update column names if your form uses different field names
- Default: "Name", "Email Address", "Inquiry"

**Tip:** Keep "includeOtherFields" enabled to preserve all form data

### üß† Step 3: AI Triage Analysis

OpenAI analyzes inquiry to determine:
- **Urgency**: low/medium/high
- **Category**: technical/sales/support/billing/general
- **Sentiment**: positive/neutral/negative
- **Keywords**: Key terms extracted
- **Summary**: One-sentence overview

**Customize:**
- Adjust urgency criteria for your business
- Add custom categories
- Supports multiple languages automatically

**Cost:** ~$0.001-0.002 per inquiry with GPT-4o-mini

### üîÄ Step 4: Priority Routing

Routes inquiries to appropriate response template:

**High Priority ‚Üí** Urgent, empathetic response
- Broken products, complaints, angry customers
- Immediate needs, refund requests

**Medium Priority ‚Üí** Professional, standard response
- General questions, usage help
- Feature inquiries

**Low Priority ‚Üí** Friendly, casual response
- Information requests, compliments
- Future product questions

### ‚úâÔ∏è Step 5: Generate AI Response

Three separate AI nodes create priority-specific responses.

**Each template considers:**
- Customer name for personalization
- Inquiry category and sentiment
- Urgency level for appropriate tone

**Output format:**
SUBJECT: (email subject)
BODY: (email body)

**Customize:** Edit prompts to match your brand voice and policies

### üì§ Step 6: Send Auto-Reply

Sends personalized email via Gmail.

**Features:**
- Uses Gmail OAuth for secure sending
- Includes customer name in email
- Professional formatting
- No n8n attribution footer

**Setup:** Connect your Gmail account via OAuth2

### üö® Step 7: Team Alerts & Tracking

**High Priority Cases:**
- Instant Slack notification to team
- Includes customer details and inquiry
- Prompts manual follow-up within 1-2 hours

**All Cases:**
- Logged to Google Sheets tracking sheet
- Includes: timestamp, urgency, category, sentiment, keywords, summary
- Creates audit trail and analytics data

**Setup:**
1. Connect Slack workspace (optional)
2. Create tracking sheet with proper column headers
3. Select channel for notifications

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
